<TITLE> One-stop passport service centre opens </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, Aug 29 (bdnews24.com) - A one- stop service centre has begun functioning at the regional passport office in Agargaon since Wednesday. Home secretary Abdul Karim Wednesday inaugurated the centre where people will be able to make changes, including in profession, date of birth, name and address, in their passports. Applicants would get necessary cooperation in completing all work regarding inclusions in the passport on the same day, in exchange for a Tk 500 fee at the centre, the Press Information Department said in a statement. Work at the centre will be conducted on a first-come-first-served basis. Women, children, elderly people and the physically challenged would be given priority. The centre will remain open from 9.30am to 1.30pm. bd
